This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it deals with techniques for inducing structured sparsity in neural networks for image classification. Additionally, it may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories, as well as the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category, as it involves optimizing the structure of neural networks to meet specific resource constraints.
